{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"1cd34845-99aa-4cf5-8ce0-771c7d67e0a7","content":"Update these three files:\n\n**1. `.csproj`** — change the target framework:\n```xml\n<TargetFramework>net11.0</TargetFramework>\n```\n\n**2. `global.json`** — pin the new SDK:\n```json\n{ \"sdk\": { \"version\": \"11.0.100\" } }\n```\n\n**3. `Dockerfile`** — update base images:\n```dockerfile\nFROM mcr.microsoft.com/dotnet/aspnet:11.0 AS base\nFROM mcr.microsoft.com/dotnet/sdk:11.0 AS build\n```\n\nThen run:\n```bash\ndotnet restore\ndotnet build\n```\n\nCheck for any breaking changes or deprecated APIs in the [.NET 11 release notes](https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/dotnet/core/whats-new/) and update any NuGet packages (e.g., `Microsoft.AspNetCore.*`, `Microsoft.EntityFrameworkCore`) to their 11.x versions.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"806bf69e-cfed-4673-8af2-249d571d8cae","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking how to update their .NET 10 ASP.NET Core web app to .NET 11. This is a straightforward question about upgrading .NET versions — I don't need to search any codebase since they're describing their setup. Let me provide a concise answer.","outputTokens":322,"requestId":"400F:56360:1671AD8:1945937:69F94B06"},"id":"a8520ace-637c-4533-8680-0c285394e5cd","timestamp":"2026-05-05T01:42:36.638Z","parentId":"bcc97ecc-1feb-4279-9603-92b3ccae2232"}
